Dialogue: 0,0:54:19.20,0:54:27.20,Default,,0,0,0,,consequence and u so you accept then\Nthat God's grace is expressing itself as
Dialogue: 0,0:54:27.20,0:54:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,allowing you to recover spiritually from\Nthe damage that you did to yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:33.04,0:54:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,People in hell do not have that option.\NThat's why you don't want to go there.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.80,0:54:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Here\Nwe have the option by uh good actions to
Dialogue: 0,0:54:45.04,0:54:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,undo\Nthe consequences of bad actions. We see
Dialogue: 0,0:54:50.16,0:54:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,it expressed\Nin
Dialogue: 0,0:54:54.07,0:54:58.07,Default,,0,0,0,,you know in sizable portions of the\Npopulation.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:58.07,0:55:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,sizable pop, you know, sizable\Nuh great numbers of people did
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.52,0:55:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,horrendous things for many many\Ncenturies,
Dialogue: 0,0:55:08.24,0:55:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,thousands of years. Great hordes of\Npeople did horrible things, did they
Dialogue: 0,0:55:12.72,0:55:17.04,Default,,0,0,0,,not?\NAnd now we see horrible things
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.04,0:55:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,happening, you know, to great hordes of\Npeople. And mankind's been at war 93% of
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.76,0:55:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the time.\NThe other 7% I never did get a chance to
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.07,0:55:33.20,Default,,0,0,0,,find out what he was up to. No good of\Nsome kind, no doubt.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.20,0:55:38.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Wasn't war, but it was probably\Nsomething else just as bad. Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:38.64,0:55:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So,\Nso the evolution of mankind has been so
Dialogue: 0,0:55:43.52,0:55:50.31,Default,,0,0,0,,out of gratitude for the willingness to\Nsurrender then is the willingness to
Dialogue: 0,0:55:50.31,0:55:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,worship God by virtue of the expression\Nof creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.55,0:56:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,That every every phenomena is an\Nexpression of the unfolding of creation.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:02.24,0:56:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore to surrender to it is\Nyou know the old saying the reed that
Dialogue: 0,0:56:08.24,0:56:13.92,Default,,0,0,0,,resists the stream breaks and the reed\Nthat bends with the stream. So you
Dialogue: 0,0:56:13.92,0:56:18.96,Default,,0,0,0,,follow the woo way you follow the way of\Nthe wisdom and you bend you bend with
Dialogue: 0,0:56:18.96,0:56:26.07,Default,,0,0,0,,it. So\Nif the regime is totalitarian, you blend
Dialogue: 0,0:56:26.07,0:56:31.92,Default,,0,0,0,,with the totalitarianism\Nand if the so whatever the regime is,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.92,0:56:36.31,Default,,0,0,0,,you blend with it and then you look for\Na way that you might shift your balance
Dialogue: 0,0:56:36.31,0:56:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,in what you think is the more favorable\Ndirection.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:42.79,0:56:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Surrendering is uh extremely easy. So if\Nyou can float in the water, anybody here
Dialogue: 0,0:56:48.00,0:56:54.16,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't know how to float probably there\Nprobably are. Come on liars, speak up.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:54.16,0:56:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I know.\NHow to float. How to just go with the
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.68,0:57:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,wind.\NAllow yourself to be
Dialogue: 0,0:57:04.07,0:57:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,uh p passive passive passive participant\Nand in surrender. So recovery from any
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.48,0:57:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,illnesses requires surrendering your\Nwill to God, taking a moral inventory,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.59,0:57:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,asking for God's help, and the\Nwillingness to surrender it which is
Dialogue: 0,0:57:22.40,0:57:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,habitually uh injurious or painful to\Nyourself or others. Yes. Is that
Dialogue: 0,0:57:27.76,0:57:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,sufficient?\NAnd there's exercises in passivity.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:36.72,0:57:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You ever do these exercises where you\Nhave three people, person in the middle,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:40.64,0:57:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a person behind him, and you\Npush him over and he has to allow
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.83,0:57:48.96,Default,,0,0,0,,himself to be caught by the other\Nperson. So that's a good practice to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:48.96,0:57:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't, if you can't figure how to\Nsurrender, you need two people, that's
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.52,0:57:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,all. And somebody pushes you this way\Nand the other person catches you. And to
Dialogue: 0,0:57:59.35,0:58:07.04,Default,,0,0,0,,allow yourself to be thrown about like a\NMidgets don't mind. It's just the
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.04,0:58:13.72,Default,,0,0,0,,viewers think it's insulting to midgets.\NMidgets don't feel that way at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:18.72,0:58:22.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Must be fun just to be thrown around.\NImagine flying through the air and
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.31,0:58:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,people are catching you. I mean, it' be\Nhilarious.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:25.35,0:58:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody else got anything they want?\NWe'll hit some other things, but let's
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.00,0:58:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,have a vote for whatever subject you\Nmight like finish. Um, I'd like for you
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.40,0:58:40.16,Default,,0,0,0,,to explain how we can do supplication in\Na non-dualistic way.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.16,0:58:45.28,Default,,0,0,0,,>> How you could do what?\N>> Supplication in a non in a unity style
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.28,0:58:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,fashion.\N>> Supplication.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:47.76,0:58:51.04,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Yeah.\N>> Non-dualistic
Dialogue: 0,0:58:51.04,0:58:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,>> in non-dualistic.\N>> Oh, supplication. Yes. Well, many of
Dialogue: 0,0:58:57.44,0:59:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,these things are nonverbal.\NAs I said, the contemplative lifestyle
Dialogue: 0,0:59:04.55,0:59:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,is one in which you see instead of\Nacquiring knowledge, you can retreat and
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.83,0:59:16.55,Default,,0,0,0,,allow for revelation. The major\Nexperiences of my life are all
Dialogue: 0,0:59:16.55,0:59:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,revelations.\NThey were preceded by let's say some
Dialogue: 0,0:59:20.48,0:59:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,great anguish within the ego of the mind\Nand etc. But the experiences were uh all
Dialogue: 0,0:59:28.96,0:59:36.72,Default,,0,0,0,,extremely yin. It was all\Na matter of standing back and allowing
Dialogue: 0,0:59:36.72,0:59:40.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that which is magnificent to reveal\Nitself.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:40.79,0:59:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,None of it was acquisition. There was no\Ngoing from here to there or from this
Dialogue: 0,0:59:45.68,0:59:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,space to that space. Uh\Nthe willingness to let go of
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.44,0:59:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,thinkingness. Well, that has to do with\Nletting go opinionation.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:56.79,1:00:02.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And you don't need an opinion on\Nanything. Yeah,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:03.68,1:00:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember a friend of mine in recovery\Nand he said, "It suddenly dawned on me,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:09.11,1:00:13.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't have to have an opinion on\Neverything." I said, "Wow, what a
Dialogue: 0,1:00:13.20,1:00:17.20,Default,,0,0,0,,relief. You don't have to have an\Nopinion on everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.20,1:00:20.64,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, you don't have to have an\Nopinion at all. You become the witness
Dialogue: 0,1:00:20.64,1:00:26.40,Default,,0,0,0,,observer." The witness observer just\Nobserves how it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:26.40,1:00:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,this survives. This doesn't survive. The\Nleaves turn brown, the leaves fall off.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:32.79,1:00:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And uh acquiescence to God's will is\Nmerely witnessing the unfoldment of
Dialogue: 0,1:00:39.76,1:00:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,evolution as creation. Creation\Nevolution are one and the same thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:45.20,1:00:52.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore allowing spontaneity.\NEverything is becoming the actuality of
Dialogue: 0,1:00:52.72,1:00:57.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that which it is.\NWhat what anything means? What does
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.59,1:01:02.24,Default,,0,0,0,,anything mean?\NAnything you can say about what a thing
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.24,1:01:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,means is idiotic.\NWhat a thing means is what it is.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.07,1:01:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Why do you have to talk about it? What\Nis the meaning of this?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.52,1:01:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,It's spoken.\NIt speaks again.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.79,1:01:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that I use it for that doesn't\Nmean that's what it means. It means what
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.64,1:01:37.28,Default,,0,0,0,,it means to me. See, so what a thing\Nmeans is identical with its existence.
